Peruvian  consumer prices  rose 0.54
percent in September, the national statistics agency said.  Prices increased 3.74 percent from the same month a year
earlier, the agency said in an e-mailed statement. The median
estimate of analysts  surveyed  by Bloomberg was for a monthly
increase of 0.45 percent and a yearly rise of 3.62 percent.  The  consumer price index  is based on an agency survey of
establishments in the Lima Metropolitan area.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
